data.title: DOD In Photos: 2023
data.meta_description: Take a look at the Defense Department and its people through the eyes of military photographers during operations, training activities, humanitarian missions and other major events of 2023.
data.text:
Double Strike

The Dwight D. Eisenhower Carrier Strike Group sails alongside the Gerald R. Ford Carrier Strike Group in support of operations in the Mediterranean Sea, Nov. 3, 2023. The U.S. maintains forward-deployed, ready and postured forces to deter aggression and support security and stability around the world.

Photo By: Navy Petty Officer 3rd Class Janae Chambers

VIRIN: 231103-N-JC256-1451A

Happy Day

A soldier reunites with a loved one in Boise, Idaho, Aug. 8, 2023, after a yearlong deployment supporting Operation Spartan Shield. The U.S. Central Command operation is designed to build partner capacity in the Middle East.

Photo By: Air National Guard Staff Sgt. Joseph Morgan

VIRIN: 230808-Z-VT588-2362C

Go With the Floe

Crew and researchers assigned to the Coast Guard cutter Healy install equipment on a multiyear ice floe in the Beaufort Sea, Aug. 9, 2023. The Healy is the Coast Guard's only icebreaker specifically designed for Arctic research.

Photo By: Coast Guard Petty Officer 3rd Class Briana Carter

VIRIN: 230809-G-HT254-1004C

All-Terrain Travelers

Airmen stationed at Incirlik Air Base, Turkey, ride all-terrain vehicles in Ürgüp, Turkey, during a trip that allowed them to experience the country's culture and history, Aug. 26, 2023.

Photo By: Air Force Staff Sgt. Michael A. Richmond

VIRIN: 230826-F-HE787-6032A

High Wire

An Air Force pararescueman executes an urban high-angle ropes maneuver to reach a simulated injured service member during the 2023 PJ Rodeo competition in Louisville, Ky., Sept. 6, 2023. The Kentucky Air National Guard's 123rd Special Tactics Squadron hosted the event, which tests the capabilities of pararescue airmen across the service.

Photo By: Dale Greer, Air National Guard

VIRIN: 230906-Z-VT419-2638

September Remembrance

A visitor pays respects to fallen service members during the Boot Memorial Hero and Remembrance Run on Ford Island in Hawaii, Sept. 10, 2023. The event honored the more than 8,000 service members who have lost their lives in combat since Sept. 11, 2001.

Photo By: Navy Petty Officer 1st Class Chris Williamson

VIRIN: 230910-N-JH293-1023W

Diving In

Retired Marine Corps Lance Cpl. Annika Hutsler participates in a swimming competition during the 2023 Invictus Games in Dusseldorf, Germany, Sept. 13, 2023. More than 500 military athletes from 21 nations competed in the games, highlighting the resilience and spirit of wounded, injured and ill service members and veterans.

Photo By: Marine Corps Cpl. Oneg Plisner

VIRIN: 230913-M-WJ192-4860M

Guest of Honor

Golda H. Fabian, a World War II Marine Corps veteran, acknowledges the crowd's applause while serving as the guest of honor for a performance by the Marine Corps Battle Color Detachment at Canby High School in Canby, Ore., March 7, 2023.

Photo By: Marine Corps Master Sgt. Rebekka Heite

VIRIN: 230307-M-NB885-1850

Balloon Recovery

Sailors recover a high-altitude surveillance balloon off the coast of Myrtle Beach, S.C., Feb. 5, 2023, a day after U.S. fighter aircraft brought it down. Partners from the Coast Guard, Federal Aviation Administration and FBI ensured public safety throughout the operation and recovery efforts.

Photo By: Navy Petty Officer 1st Class Tyler Thompson

VIRIN: 230205-N-QA919-0182Y

A Dog's Dream

Airmen throw tennis balls for Caro, a military working dog, during his retirement ceremony at Davis-Monthan Air Force Base, Ariz., March 20, 2023. Airmen honored Caro for his nine years of distinguished service to the Air Force.

Photo By: Air Force Airman 1st Class Jhade Herrera

VIRIN: 230320-F-AR459-1145

Spot the Soldiers

Soldiers climb a steep cliff during Exercise Rhodope 23 in Smolyan, Bulgaria, Sept. 18, 2023. Troops from the U.S., Bulgaria, Italy and the Czech Republic participated in the exercise, which focused on tactics and survival procedures in mountainous areas.

Photo By: Army Spc. Ubaldo Lechuga

VIRIN: 230918-A-AB216-1156

Bear-ly Comprehending

A polar bear inspects a weather buoy installed by Coast Guard cutter Healy crew members and scientists on a multiyear ice floe in the Beaufort Sea, Aug. 13, 2023.

Photo By: Coast Guard Petty Officer 1st Class Scott Bice

VIRIN: 230812-G-G0200-1004T

Tunnel Travel

A Marine walks through a tunnel during a live-fire exercise at Marine Corps Base Camp Pendleton, Calif., Oct. 3, 2023. The tunnel is used to move safely between firing ranges during the training.

Photo By: Marine Corps Lance Cpl. Francisco Angel

VIRIN: 231003-M-HE928-1207Y

Rolling Through

An Army convoy rolls through a training village with various armored vehicles during Saber Junction 23 at the Joint Multinational Readiness Center near Hohenfels, Germany, Sept. 13, 2023. Saber Junction 23, an Army exercise with NATO allies and partners, included 4,000 participants from 16 countries.

Photo By: Army Reserve 1st Sgt. Michel Sauret

VIRIN: 230913-A-TI382-1235

Free Bird

Navy Cmdr. Kacee Jossis releases an 'a'o back into the wild during an annual release and blessing of the critically endangered birds in Lihue, Hawaii, Oct. 18, 2023. 'A'os use the light from the night sky to navigate and can be thrown off track by the artificial lights on Kauai.

Photo By: Navy Petty Officer 2nd Class Louis Lea

VIRIN: 231018-N-HW207-1189
